WEBVTT

00:00.836 --> 00:03.640
[sirens wailing in distance]

00:03.664 --> 00:06.329
<i>[light instrumental music]</i>

00:06.363 --> 00:09.098
[toothbrush rasping]

00:09.133 --> 00:11.167
[knock at door]

00:12.695 --> 00:14.103
Rachel, my God!

00:14.138 --> 00:16.432
You get younger every time I see you.

00:16.470 --> 00:18.671
Oh, shut up!

00:22.746 --> 00:24.781
Mm, nice.

00:24.815 --> 00:27.183
Always the best for you, darling.

00:28.643 --> 00:30.472
Um, I'm sorry.

00:30.475 --> 00:31.643
I should have told you on the phone

00:31.645 --> 00:33.546
when we set up the appointment.

00:33.573 --> 00:36.859
Um, my fee has gone up.

00:36.894 --> 00:38.361
Well, after all this time,

00:38.395 --> 00:41.631
you should know you're
worth every penny.

00:41.665 --> 00:43.966
- I want to see you.
- Yes.

00:44.001 --> 00:46.202
- Show yourself.
- Yes.

00:48.405 --> 00:50.807
Harold, make yourself known.

00:50.841 --> 00:53.943
Rachel's here. She wants to talk to you.

00:55.274 --> 00:57.647
He's here.

00:57.681 --> 00:58.748
[chuckles]

00:58.782 --> 01:01.984
He wants you to know he
thinks the new haircut is hot.

01:02.019 --> 01:03.419
[laughs]

01:03.454 --> 01:05.188
32 years we're married.

01:05.221 --> 01:07.156
Now that you're dead, you like it short.

01:07.191 --> 01:09.726
Harold says he was stupid.

01:09.760 --> 01:11.994
- He hated change.
- God, Harold.

01:12.029 --> 01:14.864
Not a day goes by I don't
miss you something awful.

01:14.898 --> 01:17.867
He doesn't want you
to grieve him forever.

01:17.901 --> 01:19.869
He wants you to be happy.

01:21.238 --> 01:25.007
I-I need to tell you something.

01:25.042 --> 01:27.043
I'm seeing someone.

01:29.780 --> 01:31.948
He's listening. Go on.

01:31.982 --> 01:33.950
We're taking it slow,

01:33.984 --> 01:36.185
but...

01:36.220 --> 01:38.087
I'm happy.

01:38.122 --> 01:40.156
He wants to know who it is.

01:41.892 --> 01:42.892
It's Kevin.

01:42.926 --> 01:44.894
<i>[dramatic musical sting]</i>

01:44.928 --> 01:46.896
[ghostly whispers]

01:46.930 --> 01:48.197
[shivering]

01:48.232 --> 01:50.767
Well, perhaps we should take a break.

01:50.801 --> 01:52.201
[breathing heavily]

01:52.236 --> 01:54.137
Or just stop altogether.

01:54.171 --> 01:56.939
- [gasps]
- [glass shatters]

01:56.974 --> 01:59.075
[whooshing]

02:01.912 --> 02:03.446
No.

02:03.480 --> 02:05.481
[ghost growling]

02:05.516 --> 02:07.631
You are not to cross.

02:07.663 --> 02:09.931
What's wrong?

02:09.959 --> 02:12.922
Stay back. You stay back.

02:12.956 --> 02:16.893
[gagging]

02:16.927 --> 02:19.462
[gulping and panting]

02:19.496 --> 02:21.063
[whimpers]

02:21.098 --> 02:24.100
[labored breathing]

02:24.134 --> 02:27.715
[distorted voice] My partner? My friend?

02:27.743 --> 02:30.609
- Harold?
- You had to go there?

02:30.644 --> 02:31.644
- [ring clatters]
- Oh!

02:31.678 --> 02:33.438
Since when?

02:33.477 --> 02:35.748
- Did you wait till I...
- No, it's nothing like that!

02:35.782 --> 02:37.016
What's it like then?

02:37.050 --> 02:38.651
Does he like your hair like that?

02:38.685 --> 02:41.320
- No!
- Get out of my body, Harold.

02:41.354 --> 02:43.088
Ahh! [whimpering]

02:43.123 --> 02:44.757
[distorted voice] Sit!

02:44.791 --> 02:48.093
- Oh! No!
- You can be with me.

02:48.128 --> 02:49.762
We can be together again!

02:49.796 --> 02:51.930
[crying]

02:51.965 --> 02:55.034
I'm not gonna let you hurt her!

02:55.068 --> 02:57.136
I'd rather end it!

02:57.170 --> 02:59.104
You don't get another go-around, Harold.

02:59.139 --> 03:02.107
[grunting] Get... the hell... out now!

03:02.142 --> 03:04.343
[whooshing]

03:04.377 --> 03:05.811
[mirror shard clatters]

03:07.814 --> 03:10.683
[panting]

03:14.721 --> 03:17.156
[exhales] Well, I guess
Harold still hates change.

03:17.190 --> 03:18.957
[inhales, exhales]

03:18.992 --> 03:21.960
<i>[bluesy guitar music]</i>

03:21.995 --> 03:29.034
<i>♪</i>

03:30.203 --> 03:31.303
Ah.

03:37.110 --> 03:40.179
[phone vibrating]

03:45.218 --> 03:47.152
<i>You can't run from me, Manfred.</i>

03:47.187 --> 03:48.921
I'm not running. I'm paying you back.

03:48.955 --> 03:51.657
- I just need time.
<i>- Too late. I will find you.</i>

03:51.691 --> 03:52.643
Gotta go.

03:52.690 --> 03:55.394
<i>["Lonely Boy" by The Black Keys]</i>

03:55.428 --> 03:58.397
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

03:58.431 --> 04:06.405
<i>♪</i>

04:06.439 --> 04:09.675
<i>♪ Well, I'm so above you ♪</i>

04:09.709 --> 04:12.678
<i>♪ And it's plain to see ♪</i>

04:12.712 --> 04:18.016
<i>♪ But I came to love you anyway ♪</i>

04:18.051 --> 04:21.019
<i>♪ So you tore my heart out ♪</i>

04:21.053 --> 04:24.423
<i>♪ And I don't mind bleeding ♪</i>

04:24.457 --> 04:27.860
<i>♪ Any old time to keep me waiting ♪</i>

04:27.894 --> 04:29.762
<i>♪ Waiting, waiting ♪</i>

04:29.796 --> 04:30.763
[laughing]

04:30.797 --> 04:32.765
Hey, Grandma.

04:32.799 --> 04:34.032
You look terrible.

04:34.067 --> 04:36.468
Look who's talking.

04:36.503 --> 04:38.904
Don't tell me. Another hijacking?

04:38.938 --> 04:40.973
Only a second. I ended it quick.

04:41.007 --> 04:42.941
Couple of pills, headache's gone.

04:42.976 --> 04:45.210
This move will be good for you.

04:45.245 --> 04:47.479
You need to settle down.

04:47.514 --> 04:48.914
You need a home.

04:48.948 --> 04:50.449
I need to disappear.

04:50.483 --> 04:54.453
I can't think of a place
better to disappear to.

04:54.487 --> 04:57.489
You'll be safe in Midnight.

04:57.524 --> 04:58.924
That'd mean a whole lot more

04:58.958 --> 05:00.759
coming from someone who wasn't dead.

05:00.794 --> 05:01.894
[laughing]

05:01.928 --> 05:03.996
<i>♪ I'm a lonely boy ♪</i>

05:04.030 --> 05:06.799
<i>♪ Oh, whoa, oh ♪</i>

05:06.833 --> 05:09.101
<i>♪ I got a love that keeps me waitin' ♪</i>

05:09.135 --> 05:11.236
[hawk screeches]

05:11.278 --> 05:14.280
<i>[instrumental music]</i>

05:14.307 --> 05:21.413
<i>♪</i>

05:23.000 --> 05:29.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

05:31.124 --> 05:32.958
Mr. Snuggly, just wait a minute.

05:32.992 --> 05:34.293
I'm almost done.

05:34.327 --> 05:36.261
[cat meows]

05:36.296 --> 05:38.964
<i>♪</i>

05:38.998 --> 05:40.999
[scoffs]

05:41.034 --> 05:48.106
<i>♪</i>

05:51.144 --> 05:53.245
[engine turns off]

05:54.147 --> 05:56.248
[engine revs]

06:07.060 --> 06:09.228
A musician.

06:09.262 --> 06:11.063
Pawning a... trumpet?

06:11.097 --> 06:13.365
That's it. You nailed it.

06:15.368 --> 06:17.469
[sighs]

06:21.341 --> 06:24.309
<i>[mysterious music]</i>

06:24.344 --> 06:31.016
<i>♪</i>

06:31.050 --> 06:33.085
<i>- Don't cry.
- [crying]</i>

06:33.119 --> 06:35.320
<i>- It won't be long.
- I don't want to die.</i>

06:35.355 --> 06:38.991
<i>You'll be an angel up
in Heaven with God.</i>

06:39.025 --> 06:40.058
<i>We cast you out,</i>

06:40.093 --> 06:42.928
<i>every unclean spirit... [screaming]</i>

06:42.962 --> 06:45.998
<i>- Every legion!
- Wonders...</i>

06:46.032 --> 06:49.234
<i>My own children leave me here to rot!</i>

06:49.269 --> 06:51.003
<i>Go to hell!</i>

06:51.037 --> 06:52.905
<i>Company pull!</i>

06:52.939 --> 06:55.107
<i>[men shouting, gunshots]</i>

06:55.141 --> 06:58.010
<i>- Attack!
- [screaming]</i>

06:58.044 --> 07:00.879
Hey.

07:00.914 --> 07:02.881
You must be Manfred.

07:02.916 --> 07:05.217
You made good time from Dallas.

07:05.251 --> 07:08.186
No traffic the last five hours.

07:08.221 --> 07:10.155
No, there isn't.

07:13.092 --> 07:15.060
I'll show you your new home.

07:16.930 --> 07:18.130
Come on.

07:18.164 --> 07:20.032
The last tenant left the furniture.

07:20.066 --> 07:21.300
If particle board bothers you,

07:21.334 --> 07:22.935
you're welcome to come by the shop.

07:22.969 --> 07:24.603
It's f... it's fine.
I like newer things.

07:24.637 --> 07:27.072
RV out front suggests otherwise.

07:27.106 --> 07:29.041
[scoffs]

07:29.075 --> 07:30.375
Hey, I gotta come clean, man.

07:30.410 --> 07:32.377
I checked you out
before renting the house.

07:32.412 --> 07:33.612
I hope it's not a problem.

07:33.646 --> 07:34.980
That you're a psychic?

07:35.014 --> 07:36.615
No, just the opposite.

07:36.649 --> 07:38.617
I was gonna offer you
a month's free rent

07:38.651 --> 07:40.052
if you could help me out.

07:40.086 --> 07:42.621
My fiancée, well...

07:42.655 --> 07:45.090
Aubrey, she... she walked out.

07:45.124 --> 07:47.125
And she's not returning my calls...

07:47.160 --> 07:49.094
Let me stop you. It's...

07:49.128 --> 07:50.740
It's not real.

07:50.779 --> 07:52.430
I tell people what they want to hear.

07:52.432 --> 07:54.399
I'm just really good at reading people.

07:54.434 --> 07:55.634
That's all it is.

07:55.668 --> 07:58.670
Well, no harm in asking.

07:58.697 --> 08:02.232
You got the place for a month.

08:02.275 --> 08:03.642
You need it any longer...

08:03.676 --> 08:05.277
I know where to find you. Thanks.

08:05.311 --> 08:07.179
Mm-hmm.

08:07.213 --> 08:10.182
<i>[mellow folksy music]</i>

08:10.216 --> 08:12.741
<i>♪</i>

08:12.742 --> 08:15.055
_

08:28.052 --> 08:30.002
[indistinct chatter]

08:30.036 --> 08:33.171
<i>[bluesy rock plays]</i>

08:33.206 --> 08:40.178
<i>♪</i>

08:40.212 --> 08:42.381
Does this look like a Walmart?

08:42.414 --> 08:45.283
No. I don't provide crayons.

08:45.318 --> 08:47.019
Amuse your own children.

08:47.053 --> 08:50.022
<i>♪</i>

08:50.056 --> 08:53.291
I'd like to place an order to go.

08:53.326 --> 08:57.162
You're Manfred. Bobo
said he had a new tenant.

08:57.196 --> 08:59.164
I saw your RV, nice ride.

08:59.198 --> 09:02.467
I know. Real chick magnet.

09:02.502 --> 09:03.702
I'm Creek.

09:03.736 --> 09:04.975
I live behind the Gas & Go

09:05.006 --> 09:06.705
with my dad and little brother, Connor.

09:06.739 --> 09:08.707
- Cool.
- Follow me.

09:08.741 --> 09:10.509
- Where?
- The Midnighter's Room.

09:10.543 --> 09:11.710
It's where we sit.

09:11.744 --> 09:13.745
Except the Rev. He eats alone.

09:13.780 --> 09:15.839
Now that you live here, you eat with us.

09:15.871 --> 09:17.482
So if Midnighters eat there then...

09:17.517 --> 09:19.751
The rest of the folks are
ranchers, folks from Davy.

09:19.786 --> 09:21.987
- Well, I don't want to bother.
- You're not.

09:22.021 --> 09:23.067
It's usually more crowded.

09:23.084 --> 09:24.552
Folks are getting ready for tomorrow.

09:24.554 --> 09:26.390
It's the Annual Fall
Picnic. You should come.

09:26.392 --> 09:29.027
Well, if you'll be there.

09:29.062 --> 09:30.495
You meet your neighbors yet?

09:30.530 --> 09:33.331
Sort of. You're the non-musician.

09:33.366 --> 09:36.068
That's Olivia.

09:40.206 --> 09:41.540
Lemuel Bridger.

09:41.574 --> 09:44.009
You eat beef?

09:44.043 --> 09:46.011
Wouldn't have moved
to Texas if I didn't.

09:46.045 --> 09:47.212
- Do you trust me?
- No.

09:47.246 --> 09:48.780
But I'll let you pick out my dinner.

09:48.815 --> 09:51.349
You'll like it. I promise.

09:53.419 --> 09:56.221
Don't let her father see
you looking at her like that.

09:56.255 --> 09:58.757
I didn't mean any offense.

09:58.791 --> 10:01.226
- If I'm interrupting...
- You're not.

10:01.260 --> 10:04.229
<i>[bluesy rock music continues]</i>

10:04.263 --> 10:10.368
<i>♪</i>

10:10.403 --> 10:14.106
I live under the pawn
shop, work the night shift.

10:14.140 --> 10:16.108
That's very nice.

10:16.142 --> 10:19.244
He's hot. And he's real interesting.

10:19.278 --> 10:21.580
He's interesting because he's here.

10:21.614 --> 10:23.582
No family, no friends.

10:23.616 --> 10:25.417
He's running from something.

10:25.451 --> 10:27.686
Then he'll fit in just fine.

10:32.158 --> 10:34.392
- Apologies.
- For what?

10:34.427 --> 10:36.561
<i>[dramatic musical sting]</i>

10:36.596 --> 10:39.498
[wheezy breaths]

10:43.428 --> 10:46.830
[rasping breaths]

10:46.873 --> 10:48.056
[panting]

10:48.096 --> 10:49.730
It's been a while since I've eaten.

10:49.767 --> 10:52.110
I'm weak, and I was worried.

10:52.145 --> 10:55.814
They look like they could be
trouble, so I leeched energy.

10:55.848 --> 10:58.416
Leeched? What are you exactly?

10:58.451 --> 11:00.418
Vampire's one word for it.

11:00.453 --> 11:01.453
Seriously?

11:01.487 --> 11:03.288
Holy... What the hell?

11:03.322 --> 11:04.540
I'm beginning to take offense.

11:04.563 --> 11:08.260
Frankly, I'm less frightening
than those sons of Lucifer.

11:08.294 --> 11:10.562
Here. You'll feel better.

11:15.303 --> 11:16.670
Told you.

11:16.689 --> 11:18.090
[chuckles]

11:18.124 --> 11:19.257
What's so funny?

11:19.294 --> 11:22.307
Usually I'm the freak in the room.

11:22.341 --> 11:25.443
So, uh... none of this neck thing?

11:25.478 --> 11:29.114
Oh, that's always on the menu.

11:29.148 --> 11:30.749
Madonna's pot roast special.

11:33.386 --> 11:35.187
See, I told you you'd like it.

11:35.221 --> 11:37.622
So, if you want, I could
stop by your place tomorrow

11:37.657 --> 11:40.325
and we could go to the picnic.

11:40.359 --> 11:43.895
I'm not sure. I had
a big day of driving...

11:43.930 --> 11:45.330
I'm spent.

11:45.364 --> 11:47.299
You'll feel better in the morning.

11:47.333 --> 11:50.468
I'll have to miss it, but you should go.

11:50.503 --> 11:53.638
Midnight... is very
different in daylight.

11:56.709 --> 12:01.146
<i>♪ I'm gonna need someone to help me ♪</i>

12:01.180 --> 12:05.217
<i>♪ I'm gonna need somebody's hand ♪</i>

12:05.251 --> 12:09.487
<i>♪ I'm gonna need someone
to hold me down ♪</i>

12:09.522 --> 12:13.358
<i>♪ I'm gonna need someone to care ♪</i>

12:13.392 --> 12:15.493
Fiji, why don't you jump him already?

12:15.528 --> 12:16.928
That's not what I was thinking.

12:16.963 --> 12:18.429
Yeah, I know what you were thinking.

12:18.431 --> 12:20.665
I was admiring his cooking techniques.

12:20.700 --> 12:22.986
And don't make that dirty.

12:23.018 --> 12:25.604
- Why did she bring the new guy?
- 'Cause she's lonely.

12:25.638 --> 12:28.471
Don't worry. I made
him cookies. Sand tarts.

12:28.506 --> 12:29.971
If he had bad intentions,

12:29.994 --> 12:33.245
he'd be tossing those
cookies as we speak.

12:33.279 --> 12:36.214
Did you poison our new neighbor?

12:36.249 --> 12:39.517
It's not poison if he doesn't
have poisonous intentions.

12:39.552 --> 12:42.387
- [laughs]
- Rasta!

12:42.421 --> 12:44.689
What is that stupid dog going on about?

12:44.724 --> 12:47.626
- Rasta! Quiet.
- Rasta, what is it?

12:47.660 --> 12:49.527
So you want me to get you something?

12:49.562 --> 12:52.697
Oh, we'll come meet you in a second.

12:52.732 --> 12:55.433
So what do you think?
You happy you came?

12:55.468 --> 12:57.369
Yeah, you were right to get me out.

12:57.403 --> 12:59.537
Gives me a new perspective on...

12:59.572 --> 13:02.540
- [Fiji screaming]
- Fiji!

13:02.574 --> 13:04.901
[indistinct shouts]

13:04.933 --> 13:06.544
What's wrong?

13:06.579 --> 13:08.513
It's okay.

13:11.450 --> 13:14.419
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

13:14.453 --> 13:17.656
<i>♪</i>

13:17.690 --> 13:20.592
I need to report a
body. She's in the river.

13:20.626 --> 13:22.494
No, she's definitely dead.

13:22.528 --> 13:24.296
- [flies buzzing]
- She's all bloated.

13:24.330 --> 13:26.731
No, I know her. That's Aubrey.

13:26.766 --> 13:29.434
Aubrey Hamilton.

13:29.468 --> 13:31.569
[woman crying]

13:36.709 --> 13:41.729
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
-- <font color="#138CE9">www.Addic7ed.com</font> --

13:43.781 --> 13:45.822
Deputies will be coming by your homes

13:45.844 --> 13:48.329
over the next couple days
to get your statements.

13:48.331 --> 13:50.966
I don't want anybody leaving town

13:51.000 --> 13:53.969
without calling the department,
getting our permission.

13:54.003 --> 13:55.237
Understood?

13:55.271 --> 13:58.240
[indistinct murmuring]

13:58.274 --> 14:00.809
Haven't seen you before.

14:00.843 --> 14:02.911
Uh, I'm new.

14:02.945 --> 14:05.914
Just moved to Midnight.

14:05.948 --> 14:07.849
You, uh, you live here?

14:07.884 --> 14:10.919
Heck no. I live in Davy.

14:10.953 --> 14:13.855
Work with the Roca Fria
County Sheriff's department.

14:13.890 --> 14:15.924
Midnight's just in our jurisdiction.

14:15.958 --> 14:18.894
Why Midnight? Why would you move here?

14:18.928 --> 14:21.062
Uh, it's, um, quiet.

14:21.097 --> 14:22.685
- And cheap.
- A reason for that.

14:22.693 --> 14:24.231
Truth is, I'm surprised
this kind of thing

14:24.233 --> 14:25.200
hasn't happened before.

14:25.234 --> 14:27.769
- <i>Kind</i> of thing?
- Occult murder.

14:27.803 --> 14:29.938
You know, the kids in Davy,

14:29.972 --> 14:32.407
they dare one another to walk
Witch Light Road on full moons.

14:32.441 --> 14:36.077
It's got a bit of a ghost town
vibe, but people seem nice.

14:36.112 --> 14:37.846
Do they?

14:37.880 --> 14:39.948
Some folks say she's a witch.

14:39.982 --> 14:41.349
Or a lesbian.

14:41.384 --> 14:44.085
Could be both.

14:44.120 --> 14:45.360
Well, I wouldn't be surprised

14:45.388 --> 14:47.856
to find a skin suit in that pawn shop.

14:47.890 --> 14:49.057
Her next of kin?

14:49.091 --> 14:51.293
Me, I suppose. She's got an aunt.

14:51.327 --> 14:53.061
Raised her after her parents died.

14:53.095 --> 14:54.396
I-I don't know her name.

14:54.430 --> 14:56.932
So she was gone for two weeks.

14:56.966 --> 14:58.322
You didn't report her missing.

14:58.330 --> 15:00.235
- I thought she walked out.
- Forgot her stuff.

15:00.269 --> 15:02.103
Well, she didn't have much stuff.

15:02.138 --> 15:04.105
- Couple suitcases of clothes.
- Why'd she leave?

15:04.140 --> 15:08.443
Well, we fought. And, uh...

15:08.477 --> 15:10.812
and I got mean.

15:10.846 --> 15:13.148
You know, and I... And
I-I told her to get out.

15:13.182 --> 15:16.418
But, Sheriff, I didn't intend for that.

15:16.452 --> 15:18.253
- Poor thing.
- He better shut up

15:18.287 --> 15:20.322
before he says something
he can't take back.

15:20.356 --> 15:22.824
<i>[police radio chatter]</i>

15:22.858 --> 15:25.520
Even dead, the bitch is trouble.

15:31.133 --> 15:34.235
[water dripping]

15:44.880 --> 15:47.248
[shivering]

15:47.283 --> 15:49.851
<i>[eerie music]</i>

15:49.885 --> 15:53.455
[flies buzzing]

15:53.489 --> 15:58.193
<i>♪</i>

15:58.227 --> 16:00.028
<i>[dramatic musical sting]</i>

16:00.062 --> 16:01.029
[gasping]

16:01.063 --> 16:02.497
[water splashing]

16:02.539 --> 16:09.012
<i>♪</i>

16:09.038 --> 16:13.441
Aubrey, you don't belong here.

16:13.476 --> 16:15.143
I didn't give you permission.

16:15.177 --> 16:16.378
Go away. [whimpering]

16:16.412 --> 16:18.380
Go away!

16:18.414 --> 16:20.115
[water splashing]

16:20.149 --> 16:22.183
[gurgling]

16:22.218 --> 16:29.290
<i>♪</i>

16:33.770 --> 16:35.891
_

16:40.236 --> 16:42.971
If it means you go away,

16:43.005 --> 16:47.542
fine, but my way.

16:47.576 --> 16:49.044
Precautions in place.

16:49.078 --> 16:51.312
[gurgling, mumbling]

16:56.452 --> 17:00.221
<i>Bobo Winthrop, I love you.</i>

17:00.256 --> 17:03.491
<i>Well, I'm here with my
beautiful girlfriend</i>

17:03.526 --> 17:05.326
<i>and I was hoping that</i>

17:05.361 --> 17:08.997
<i>you would do me the honor
of becoming my wife.</i>

17:09.031 --> 17:12.500
<i>Aubrey, marry me.</i>

17:12.535 --> 17:15.103
<i>- Yes, I'll marry you!
- Yes?</i>

17:15.137 --> 17:18.106
<i>Yes, I'll be your wife! Yes!</i>

17:18.140 --> 17:20.241
<i>- She said yes!
- Look, look!</i>

17:20.276 --> 17:22.109
<i>It's so beautiful.</i>

17:22.144 --> 17:25.380
<i>Honey, you are the most beautiful girl</i>

17:25.414 --> 17:27.182
<i>I have ever laid eyes on</i>

17:27.215 --> 17:30.285
<i>and thank you for making
an honest man of me.</i>

17:30.288 --> 17:32.990
<i>Oh, fits perfectly.</i>

17:32.993 --> 17:33.893
<i>[both laughing]</i>

17:33.896 --> 17:36.391
<i>- All righty.
- [both laughing]</i>

17:36.425 --> 17:37.425
<i>I love it!</i>

17:37.460 --> 17:39.260
[soft clunk]

17:39.295 --> 17:41.262
I brought you breakfast.

17:41.297 --> 17:43.598
I can't eat.

17:43.632 --> 17:46.898
How about I keep you company then?

17:50.172 --> 17:52.407
We don't have to talk.
I'll just sit here.

17:54.310 --> 17:56.211
That'd be nice.

17:58.347 --> 18:01.316
[crows cawing]

18:01.350 --> 18:04.319
<i>[instrumental music]</i>

18:04.353 --> 18:11.459
<i>♪</i>

18:22.304 --> 18:24.572
[water bubbling]

18:24.607 --> 18:27.175
<i>[dramatic musical sting]</i>

18:27.209 --> 18:29.377
Taking holy water?

18:30.613 --> 18:34.315
Yeah. Yes, I-I am.

18:34.350 --> 18:37.085
Reverend, I'm... Manfred.

18:37.119 --> 18:39.420
I know who you are.

18:54.570 --> 18:57.038
Sunday service starts at 8:00,

18:57.072 --> 18:59.307
if you're interested.

19:03.579 --> 19:06.481
- She wanted four kids.
- Four?

19:06.515 --> 19:08.283
I told her she was crazy.

19:08.317 --> 19:11.286
But, you know, I'm open to compromise.

19:11.320 --> 19:12.640
- Of course.
- We could get a dog.

19:12.655 --> 19:14.522
[both laughing]

19:14.557 --> 19:16.658
- [clears throat]
- Sheriff Livingston.

19:16.692 --> 19:20.361
- I need to talk to Bobo.
- Okay, um, I'll go.

19:20.396 --> 19:22.230
No, could you stay?

19:22.264 --> 19:23.631
Yeah.

19:23.666 --> 19:26.234
We got the coroner's preliminary report.

19:26.268 --> 19:28.570
Single gunshot to the abdomen.

19:28.604 --> 19:31.239
But the official cause
of death was drowning.

19:31.273 --> 19:33.641
Who would do that? Who would hurt her?

19:33.676 --> 19:37.545
Aubrey wasn't... who you thought.

19:37.580 --> 19:41.416
Her real name... Aubrey Hamilton-Lowry.

19:41.450 --> 19:44.252
What are you talking about?

19:44.286 --> 19:47.488
That doesn't make any
sense. She was engaged to me.

19:53.128 --> 19:55.263
She was married five years ago.

19:55.297 --> 19:57.098
Sons of Lucifer.

19:57.132 --> 19:58.566
So a white supremacist?

19:58.601 --> 20:00.401
Name's Peter Lowry.

20:00.436 --> 20:02.437
He just got out of Beaumont Federal.

20:02.471 --> 20:04.105
Served three years for assault.

20:04.139 --> 20:05.740
Let me guess. You can't find him.

20:05.774 --> 20:09.277
He's Sons of Lucifer. He's protected.

20:09.311 --> 20:11.412
He's got reach.

20:11.447 --> 20:15.683
You Midnighters, you like to
take care of things yourselves,

20:15.718 --> 20:18.286
but in this case, don't.

20:18.320 --> 20:21.689
If he shows up here, you call us.

20:22.758 --> 20:24.692
Understood.

20:30.332 --> 20:33.301
<i>[tense music]</i>

20:33.335 --> 20:40.441
<i>♪</i>

20:44.346 --> 20:45.713
[exhales]

20:47.349 --> 20:50.451
Don't be coy.

20:50.486 --> 20:53.454
[whooshing]

20:53.489 --> 20:56.557
[water bubbling]

21:01.430 --> 21:03.665
Stay on that side.

21:03.699 --> 21:07.302
[gurgling]

21:16.345 --> 21:18.346
What is it you need to tell me?

21:18.380 --> 21:24.786
<i>♪</i>

21:24.820 --> 21:27.622
Hey, whoa, whoa, slower. Slower.

21:27.656 --> 21:32.293
<i>♪</i>

21:32.328 --> 21:35.196
P.

21:35.230 --> 21:38.266
E. C. A.

21:38.300 --> 21:40.301
D.

21:40.336 --> 21:42.370
O.

21:42.404 --> 21:43.671
S.

21:43.706 --> 21:45.673
Pecados.

21:45.708 --> 21:48.776
<i>[screaming]</i>

21:48.811 --> 21:50.378
A friend of yours?

21:50.412 --> 21:52.547
[gunshot]

21:52.581 --> 21:55.516
<i>I was wrong. Made a mistake.</i>

21:55.551 --> 21:56.818
<i>I don't want to die.</i>

21:56.852 --> 21:58.853
<i>[sobbing]</i>

21:58.887 --> 22:01.556
<i>[woman screaming]</i>

22:01.590 --> 22:04.659
No, I called for Aubrey,
not the rest of you.

22:04.693 --> 22:06.294
You're all unwelcome in my...

22:06.328 --> 22:09.430
[sinister growling]

22:12.334 --> 22:16.371
<i>[indistinct chanting]</i>

22:16.405 --> 22:18.506
This is my home.

22:18.540 --> 22:20.241
You have no right...

22:20.275 --> 22:21.376
<i>Die.</i>

22:25.447 --> 22:29.684
<i>I made a mistake! I don't want to die!</i>

22:29.718 --> 22:30.818
<i>[screaming]</i>

22:33.459 --> 22:36.687
[flies buzzing]

22:36.721 --> 22:39.690
<i>[eerie music]</i>

22:39.731 --> 22:44.335
<i>♪</i>

22:44.362 --> 22:47.331
<i>[Western rock music]</i>

22:47.365 --> 22:54.472
<i>♪</i>

23:04.583 --> 23:06.116
I didn't see you at the picnic.

23:06.151 --> 23:07.818
I don't eat barbeque.

23:07.853 --> 23:09.119
Did you know Aubrey Hamilton?

23:09.154 --> 23:12.690
Came in and prayed from time to time.

23:12.724 --> 23:15.693
But she wanted to talk to God, not me.

23:15.727 --> 23:17.412
<i>She was a sweet girl.</i>

23:17.463 --> 23:20.298
Even though she pretty much
lied to you about everything?

23:20.326 --> 23:24.134
Well, what I meant was...

23:24.169 --> 23:27.872
I thought she was sweet until
I knew she was duplicitous.

23:27.906 --> 23:31.742
Well, the crime scene
was, uh, ritualistic...

23:31.776 --> 23:34.044
Animal remains, bones.

23:34.079 --> 23:35.946
I thought that was curious.

23:37.048 --> 23:38.983
Curious, no.

23:39.017 --> 23:41.018
It's wicked and sad.

23:41.052 --> 23:43.721
Witchcraft. That's your thing, right?

23:43.755 --> 23:45.022
Wicca.

23:45.056 --> 23:48.058
Lot of animal sacrifices in that Wicca?

23:48.093 --> 23:50.895
Bundy and Dahmer, Son of Sam...

23:50.929 --> 23:52.430
All of them started out with critters

23:52.454 --> 23:55.599
before they killed people,
and not a Wiccan in the bunch.

23:55.642 --> 23:58.610
She'd always come in
with some Pinterest board.

23:58.637 --> 24:00.404
Stripper trendy was her aesthetic.

24:00.438 --> 24:03.173
Okay, so when she did come in,
did she ever confide in you?

24:03.208 --> 24:05.042
Talk about Bobo?

24:05.076 --> 24:07.912
You mean, like girl talk?

24:07.946 --> 24:09.680
Aubrey didn't talk.

24:09.714 --> 24:11.181
She liked how I did her nails.

24:12.519 --> 24:13.786
Damn it.

24:13.820 --> 24:16.789
<i>[edgy music]</i>

24:16.823 --> 24:20.659
<i>♪</i>

24:20.693 --> 24:21.994
Hello again.

24:22.028 --> 24:23.896
I need to take your
statement, Mr. Bernardo.

24:23.930 --> 24:26.632
She didn't approve of our lifestyle.

24:26.666 --> 24:28.901
Didn't like the fact
that Chuy was Mexican.

24:28.935 --> 24:31.770
So it was safe to say that
you didn't like the girl?

24:31.805 --> 24:33.939
She judged me, I didn't
like how that made me feel.

24:33.973 --> 24:36.308
So I didn't judge her.

24:36.349 --> 24:38.317
The Christian way, right?

24:38.344 --> 24:39.645
I just moved here.

24:39.670 --> 24:41.213
I have nothing do to with any of this.

24:41.246 --> 24:42.847
I'd like to take a look
around, if you don't mind.

24:42.849 --> 24:44.750
Uh, actually, I do mind. I mind a lot.

24:44.784 --> 24:46.652
- Why?
- 'Cause you're acting weird.

24:46.686 --> 24:48.754
And you lie to people for a living.

24:48.788 --> 24:50.022
[fly buzzes]

24:50.056 --> 24:53.659
I don't. I can prove it.

24:53.693 --> 24:55.928
Does "Pecados" mean anything to you?

25:00.066 --> 25:04.002
Now, I've heard of departments
consulting with psychics.

25:04.037 --> 25:06.972
I never put much stock in it.

25:07.006 --> 25:09.975
My grandmother did it all the time.

25:10.009 --> 25:12.344
I got a Magic 8-Ball.

25:12.378 --> 25:13.846
Maybe I should shake it,

25:13.880 --> 25:15.781
figure out who stole Levi's Subaru.

25:15.806 --> 25:17.941
[laughs]

25:17.984 --> 25:19.702
Hey, we got something!

25:23.723 --> 25:25.958
Could your 8-Ball do that?

25:31.097 --> 25:34.066
<i>[tense music]</i>

25:34.100 --> 25:37.517
<i>♪</i>

25:37.540 --> 25:39.604
I already have consultations
scheduled in Phoenix...

25:39.606 --> 25:40.548
Cancel them.

25:40.563 --> 25:41.939
You're part of this investigation.

25:41.941 --> 25:43.709
Don't leave town.

25:44.611 --> 25:46.078
[cat purrs]

25:46.112 --> 25:48.881
<i>You said I'd be safe.</i>

25:48.915 --> 25:53.151
Well, I thought you'd lay low,
not conjure up angry ghosts.

25:53.177 --> 25:55.845
I conjured one ghost.
Not a crowd of 'em.

25:55.889 --> 25:59.725
Certainly not whatever
that was under that floor.

25:59.759 --> 26:02.728
Midnight's not the same as most places.

26:02.762 --> 26:05.434
Which is why I need to get
the hell out as soon as...

26:05.466 --> 26:07.567
possible.

26:10.203 --> 26:12.004
- Olivia.
- You okay?

26:12.038 --> 26:14.039
- I-I heard voices.
- You did.

26:14.073 --> 26:15.774
Me. On the phone.

26:15.808 --> 26:17.609
- Oh.
- So, uh...

26:17.644 --> 26:19.110
I'm surprised. I thought
you were avoiding me.

26:19.112 --> 26:22.514
I was. Till now.

26:25.318 --> 26:27.742
- [knocking at door]
- Coming.

26:27.785 --> 26:29.352
It's late.

26:29.386 --> 26:31.487
I know. I'm sorry. I'm worried...

26:31.522 --> 26:33.623
- [thud, muffled grunt]
- What was that?

26:33.657 --> 26:35.124
[muffled groaning]

26:35.159 --> 26:36.492
Olivia,

26:36.527 --> 26:38.428
deal with your anger issues.

26:38.462 --> 26:40.142
Ugh, help me get him up.

26:40.158 --> 26:42.465
Why exactly is he naked?

26:42.499 --> 26:45.535
I was checking for wires, GPS trackers.

26:45.569 --> 26:48.771
We live such different lives.

26:48.806 --> 26:50.023
This is unexpected.

26:50.054 --> 26:51.506
Oh, well, now that
you're done sleeping in,

26:51.508 --> 26:52.942
how 'bout some help?

26:52.945 --> 26:54.367
Ahh!

26:54.370 --> 26:56.377
Looks like I'm just in time for the fun.

26:56.380 --> 26:58.481
Hundreds of Podunk towns in Texas.

26:58.515 --> 27:00.783
- Why ours?
- Luck, I suppose.

27:00.818 --> 27:03.034
Do you work for the police
or any law enforcement agency?

27:03.036 --> 27:04.418
- No.
- Were you sent here

27:04.421 --> 27:05.655
- to find someone?
- No.

27:05.689 --> 27:08.491
- Did my dad send you?
- Y-your dad? No!

27:08.525 --> 27:12.462
I'm getting bored and hungry.

27:12.496 --> 27:14.797
Okeydoke, this could
go sideways real fast.

27:14.832 --> 27:17.700
I don't want that. You don't want that.

27:17.735 --> 27:19.502
I'm good either way.

27:19.536 --> 27:21.671
I'm here 'cause my
grandma got a feeling.

27:21.705 --> 27:23.907
A psychic feeling that I'd be safe here.

27:23.941 --> 27:25.742
Her reads are usually spot-on

27:25.776 --> 27:28.319
but Xylda's also a pathological
liar, so there's that.

27:28.335 --> 27:30.380
Xylda? Gypsy Xylda?

27:30.414 --> 27:32.482
- You... you know my grandma?
- I do.

27:32.516 --> 27:35.551
- How's she doing?
- Dead.

27:35.586 --> 27:37.553
Going on a year now. Throat cancer.

27:37.588 --> 27:39.756
After a run-in with someone
who tried to kill me,

27:39.790 --> 27:41.691
Xylda said I should hide here.

27:41.725 --> 27:44.694
Who are you hiding from, and
why do they want you dead?

27:44.728 --> 27:47.563
Really wants Xylda dead,
but it's too late for that.

27:47.598 --> 27:50.221
I guess I'm the only one
left to get payback from.

27:50.263 --> 27:52.931
Who'd want to hurt Xylda?

27:52.965 --> 27:56.335
She ran scams, removed
fake hexes, curses,

27:56.369 --> 27:58.337
stole and spent more than $2 million.

27:58.371 --> 28:01.106
Still doesn't explain why he's
so chummy with the sheriff.

28:01.140 --> 28:02.322
They showed up my door.

28:02.353 --> 28:03.647
I didn't want to give them my secrets.

28:03.649 --> 28:04.983
So I gave 'em Aubrey's.

28:05.009 --> 28:06.776
I-I'm done with the questions

28:06.825 --> 28:08.793
and getting punched
in the face, thank you.

28:08.806 --> 28:11.149
So either end it already

28:11.184 --> 28:13.151
or let me get dressed.

28:13.186 --> 28:15.723
Untie him.

28:15.778 --> 28:17.824
- He's one of us.
- [sighs]

28:17.858 --> 28:19.125
Midnight has been a haven

28:19.160 --> 28:21.294
for people like us for centuries.

28:21.329 --> 28:25.611
Some, like Xylda, stop
for a bit and move on.

28:25.655 --> 28:27.656
Others, like us, make this home.

28:27.705 --> 28:30.170
Wait, everyone here is..

28:30.204 --> 28:32.305
- What are you?
- None of your business.

28:32.340 --> 28:33.907
Olivia's a friend.

28:33.941 --> 28:37.077
Her, Bobo, human, but open-minded.

28:37.110 --> 28:38.718
Your grandma wasn't wrong.

28:38.742 --> 28:40.914
If you can stand the
summers and the neighbors,

28:40.948 --> 28:42.849
Midnight is pretty safe.

28:42.883 --> 28:44.150
As long as we're quiet,

28:44.185 --> 28:46.253
cops and regular folks
tolerate us, but...

28:46.287 --> 28:47.921
The bitch dying isn't quiet.

28:47.955 --> 28:50.724
And with the police and media digging,

28:50.758 --> 28:53.026
torches and pitchforks
aren't far behind.

28:53.060 --> 28:55.393
Question: you said people
like us are drawn here.

28:55.409 --> 28:56.862
What's so special about this place?

28:56.864 --> 29:01.067
Oh, well, Midnight sits on
powerful mystical energy.

29:01.102 --> 29:04.871
The veil between the living
and the dead is awful thin here.

29:04.905 --> 29:08.742
- Oh.
- Oh, what?

29:08.784 --> 29:12.359
Oh, I get why Xylda
liked this place so much.

29:12.391 --> 29:15.215
You want me to get some
salve for your face?

29:15.249 --> 29:17.117
No, I just want to go home.

29:17.151 --> 29:20.854
Of course. Apologies for
the little misunderstanding.

29:20.888 --> 29:24.291
This is usually a
quiet and peaceful town.

29:24.325 --> 29:27.294
<i>[upbeat dramatic music]</i>

29:27.328 --> 29:34.601
<i>♪</i>

29:36.236 --> 29:37.937
Looking for me?

29:37.940 --> 29:38.956
So you killed Aubrey

29:38.959 --> 29:40.606
because you found out
the truth about her?

29:40.608 --> 29:41.860
You're not welcome here.

29:41.863 --> 29:43.810
'Cause we know the truth about you.

29:43.844 --> 29:46.212
Where'd you hide the weapons, the money?

29:46.247 --> 29:48.815
They don't belong to
you. Tell me that...

29:48.849 --> 29:50.917
maybe you live to see sunrise.

29:50.951 --> 29:53.953
I think you misjudged the situation.

29:53.988 --> 29:57.624
- [scoffs]
- I don't care either way.

30:01.128 --> 30:03.196
[gunshots]

30:05.966 --> 30:08.268
[screaming]

30:08.302 --> 30:10.070
I didn't ask for your help, man.

30:10.104 --> 30:12.105
Well, this isn't just about you anymore.

30:12.139 --> 30:14.007
Aubrey is not worth dying for.

30:14.041 --> 30:17.310
Now you go on home.
It's my shift anyway.

30:17.345 --> 30:20.313
[muffled grunting]

30:20.348 --> 30:22.148
You're welcome.

30:23.217 --> 30:25.652
- Can you deal with that?
- Sure.

30:27.121 --> 30:28.955
[screaming]

30:28.989 --> 30:31.124
[groaning]

30:31.158 --> 30:33.126
I need a word.

30:33.168 --> 30:34.618
Ahh!

30:34.658 --> 30:37.630
I'm gonna make you the same
offer you gave my friend.

30:37.665 --> 30:39.933
If you tell me who sent you,

30:39.967 --> 30:42.720
then you get to live to see the sunrise.

30:42.751 --> 30:45.038
You want a war, old man, you got one.

30:45.072 --> 30:47.941
God forgives. The Sons of Lucifer don't.

30:47.975 --> 30:49.649
Aah!

30:49.652 --> 30:51.176
My brothers are gonna come through

30:51.178 --> 30:53.346
and burn this damn place to the ground.

30:53.381 --> 30:55.281
- It's getting late.
- Aah!

30:55.316 --> 30:58.318
No sunrise for you,

30:58.352 --> 31:01.688
but a warm dinner for me.

31:03.190 --> 31:05.258
Aah!

31:13.085 --> 31:14.585
- Hey.
- Hey.

31:14.620 --> 31:17.588
<i>[country western music in background]</i>

31:17.639 --> 31:21.008
<i>♪</i>

31:21.756 --> 31:23.757
What in the world happened to you?

31:23.792 --> 31:26.326
I wish I had some sexy story to tell.

31:26.361 --> 31:29.596
It's just, uh... me,
a box, and a high shelf.

31:29.631 --> 31:32.049
Uh, a heavy box, apparently.

31:32.088 --> 31:33.467
Very.

31:33.501 --> 31:35.235
Haven't seen you since the picnic.

31:35.270 --> 31:38.238
You, uh, you okay?

31:38.273 --> 31:40.441
I can't stop thinking about it.

31:42.777 --> 31:44.812
That be all for you today?

31:44.846 --> 31:47.247
Uh... yep.

31:47.282 --> 31:48.749
Take a break, honey.

31:48.783 --> 31:50.451
Great. Thanks, Dad.

31:51.853 --> 31:54.254
What were you talking to her about?

31:54.289 --> 31:56.323
Being... neighborly.

31:56.357 --> 31:57.591
Pleasantries.

31:57.625 --> 32:00.627
That better be all.

32:00.662 --> 32:02.329
[cash register dings]

32:02.363 --> 32:03.731
That'll be $12.50.

32:10.305 --> 32:13.273
<i>[eerie music]</i>

32:13.308 --> 32:20.280
<i>♪</i>

32:20.315 --> 32:23.450
[liquid dripping]

32:23.485 --> 32:30.591
<i>♪</i>

32:39.434 --> 32:42.503
[phone vibrating]

32:46.708 --> 32:48.408
Hello?

32:48.443 --> 32:50.644
<i>I know you're in Texas.</i>

32:50.678 --> 32:52.813
<i>You were in Dallas.</i>

32:52.847 --> 32:55.482
<i>I'm getting closer.</i>

32:57.719 --> 32:59.653
[sighs]

33:03.591 --> 33:04.691
[knock at door]

33:08.730 --> 33:10.330
- Hey.
- Hey.

33:10.365 --> 33:12.107
I stopped by your house, but...

33:12.139 --> 33:14.568
Uh, yeah, lot of flies, bugs.

33:14.602 --> 33:17.131
I'll talk to Bobo if I decide to stay.

33:17.154 --> 33:18.872
Oh.

33:18.907 --> 33:21.842
Well, I just wanted to
apologize for before.

33:21.876 --> 33:24.444
My dad's weird and I didn't want
to get into a thing with him,

33:24.479 --> 33:26.346
so if I was cold to you, that's why.

33:26.381 --> 33:29.383
Yeah, no apology necessary. We're good.

33:29.417 --> 33:33.587
Oh, good. I'm glad we're good.

33:33.621 --> 33:35.856
Uh, well, since you came all this way,

33:35.890 --> 33:38.692
you want to have a beer?

33:38.726 --> 33:41.361
I guess, yeah.

33:41.396 --> 33:44.698
I gotta admit, this place
is nothing like I thought.

33:44.732 --> 33:46.633
Yeah, it's its own thing.

33:46.668 --> 33:48.435
- Makes for good stories, though.
- Stories?

33:48.469 --> 33:51.705
- You a writer?
- I write, but no.

33:51.739 --> 33:52.873
I'm not a writer.

33:52.907 --> 33:54.743
Someday, I'll go back to school.

33:54.790 --> 33:56.543
Once Connor's out of the house

33:56.578 --> 33:58.612
'cause my dad would be real tough solo.

33:58.646 --> 34:02.749
Yeah, that, uh, can't be easy for you.

34:02.784 --> 34:05.179
He wasn't always like that.

34:05.218 --> 34:07.745
After Mom died, he changed.
It's why we're here.

34:07.779 --> 34:10.614
He didn't want to live anywhere
that reminded him of her.

34:14.652 --> 34:16.754
Going to high school in Davy sucked.

34:16.788 --> 34:20.324
I was known as the chick
who lived with freaks.

34:20.358 --> 34:22.259
Okay, fine.

34:22.293 --> 34:24.360
Not that far off. Doesn't matter.

34:24.396 --> 34:27.297
After all this time, they're family.

34:27.331 --> 34:28.699
I know what Lem is.

34:28.734 --> 34:31.635
He's not the only one with secrets.

34:31.670 --> 34:34.772
<i>Like Joe, from the tattoo parlor,</i>

34:34.806 --> 34:37.141
<i>he watches over everyone.</i>

34:41.567 --> 34:44.668
[grunting]

34:59.364 --> 35:02.600
<i>You can always count on him to help.</i>

35:07.372 --> 35:10.808
<i>I wonder what brought him
and Chuy to this place.</i>

35:16.715 --> 35:18.649
<i>Bobo never talks about family</i>

35:18.683 --> 35:20.484
<i>or where he came from,</i>

35:20.519 --> 35:22.553
<i>but he's sweet and kind.</i>

35:22.587 --> 35:26.690
<i>And you will never meet a
more honest person than Bobo.</i>

35:26.725 --> 35:29.426
<i>The Rev, I still haven't figured him out.</i>

35:29.461 --> 35:31.829
<i>I've seen him pull a gravestone
out of the ground</i>

35:31.863 --> 35:33.491
<i>with one hand</i>

35:33.531 --> 35:37.368
<i>and he's completely obsessed
with his pet cemetery.</i>

35:37.402 --> 35:41.839
<i>I know Fiji's more than
just a New Age cat lady,</i>

35:41.873 --> 35:44.742
<i>but she doesn't have a
mean bone in her body.</i>

35:48.613 --> 35:50.848
Rev's gearing up.

35:50.882 --> 35:53.717
Case you didn't notice. I'm busy.

35:55.620 --> 35:56.687
Ah.

35:56.721 --> 35:58.756
Whatever you're doing there,

35:58.790 --> 36:01.358
won't do no good.

36:01.384 --> 36:03.718
I'm telling ya.

36:03.762 --> 36:07.231
Aubrey left a heap of
badness in her wake.

36:09.634 --> 36:13.437
Rancid smell of burning
hair won't change that.

36:16.474 --> 36:18.809
Yeah, keep waving them feathers.

36:18.844 --> 36:21.745
You can leave now.

36:21.780 --> 36:23.581
[purring] All right,
I'm going over there.

36:23.615 --> 36:25.950
<i>And then there's Olivia.</i>

36:25.984 --> 36:27.885
<i>She's got more secrets than anyone.</i>

36:27.919 --> 36:31.388
I understand it's a lot of money.

36:31.423 --> 36:34.592
Well, I still need to pass.

36:34.626 --> 36:35.893
[sighs]

36:35.927 --> 36:37.695
Thanks.

36:49.007 --> 36:51.909
Just checking. How'd the disposal go?

36:51.943 --> 36:54.511
Good. No one will find the body.

36:54.546 --> 36:56.981
So... who was on the phone?

36:57.015 --> 36:59.850
Job offer. A simple hit.

36:59.885 --> 37:01.785
Nice payday.

37:01.820 --> 37:03.587
But since I have to call the police

37:03.622 --> 37:05.522
every time I want to leave town,

37:05.557 --> 37:06.991
I had to say no.

37:07.025 --> 37:09.827
You seem angry.

37:09.861 --> 37:12.796
That's an understatement.

37:12.831 --> 37:16.300
Perhaps I can take
some of that from you.

37:20.038 --> 37:22.806
I was wondering when you'd ask.

37:26.478 --> 37:30.848
<i>♪</i>

37:30.882 --> 37:33.951
[heartbeat thumping]

37:37.856 --> 37:40.024
[heartbeat slows down]

37:40.058 --> 37:41.325
[moans]

37:42.396 --> 37:45.131
Midnight's weird, but it's home.

37:45.152 --> 37:49.433
Yeah, never lived in any
one place for very long.

37:49.473 --> 37:51.503
- There.
- Thanks.

37:51.536 --> 37:53.504
Well, you fit in pretty well here.

37:53.538 --> 37:55.706
- You saying I'm weird?
- You are.

37:55.740 --> 37:57.641
I Googled you, Mr. Psychic.

37:57.676 --> 38:00.511
[scoffs] It's a family business.

38:00.545 --> 38:05.349
I come from a long line
of gypsy fortune-tellers.

38:05.383 --> 38:07.551
Yeah, you have the caravan to prove it.

38:07.585 --> 38:09.086
Yep.

38:09.120 --> 38:12.556
So are you for real?

38:12.590 --> 38:15.659
Sometimes it's real.

38:15.694 --> 38:18.529
Lot of times, it's theater.

38:18.563 --> 38:20.597
Do you want to give me a reading?

38:20.632 --> 38:22.666
- No.
- Tell me my future?

38:22.701 --> 38:25.002
[sighs] Okay.

38:25.036 --> 38:26.937
Um, I'll go old-school.

38:26.972 --> 38:29.540
- Just give me your hand.
- Okay.

38:29.574 --> 38:32.543
<i>[soft pop music in background]</i>

38:32.577 --> 38:36.513
<i>♪</i>

38:36.548 --> 38:40.551
Your life line's long, varied.

38:40.585 --> 38:43.087
Will be an interesting life.

38:43.121 --> 38:47.057
You're, uh... You're
going to see the world.

38:47.092 --> 38:52.029
Uh, and here, you'll
meet your soul mate.

38:52.063 --> 38:54.031
Ah, you may already have.

38:54.065 --> 38:57.034
Someone who...

38:57.068 --> 38:59.870
sees how special you really are.

39:03.775 --> 39:07.378
That's the theater part, right?

39:07.412 --> 39:08.579
Busted.

39:08.613 --> 39:10.714
[both chuckle]

39:13.834 --> 39:17.303
Well, if you were gonna kiss
me, now would be a good time.

39:17.338 --> 39:24.128
<i>♪</i>

39:32.137 --> 39:35.139
<i>[ominous music]</i>

39:35.173 --> 39:41.478
<i>♪</i>

39:41.513 --> 39:43.447
Bobo Winthrop,

39:43.481 --> 39:45.449
you're under arrest

39:45.483 --> 39:48.163
for the murder of
Aubrey Hamilton-Lowry.

39:48.195 --> 39:49.486
I didn't kill her!

39:49.521 --> 39:51.188
You have the right to remain silent.

39:51.222 --> 39:53.157
- I did not kill her!
- Anything you say...

39:53.191 --> 39:55.191
can and will be used against
you in a court of law.

39:55.193 --> 39:56.427
- No, no!
- You have the right

39:56.461 --> 39:58.595
to an attorney.

39:58.630 --> 40:00.464
If you cannot afford an attorney,

40:00.498 --> 40:02.032
one will be appointed for you.

40:02.067 --> 40:04.168
Now do you understand these rights

40:04.202 --> 40:05.769
as I've explained them to you?

40:05.804 --> 40:07.749
It's not my first rodeo
and I am telling you,

40:07.752 --> 40:08.839
I did not do this.

40:08.873 --> 40:10.473
We've got evidence that says otherwise.

40:10.475 --> 40:11.936
- Back up. Back up!
- Let him go!

40:11.939 --> 40:13.424
- No!
- Please!

40:13.494 --> 40:14.545
Back off.

40:14.579 --> 40:16.353
- Everybody, go home.
- [gun cocks]

40:16.385 --> 40:19.183
He would never kill her. He loved her!

40:19.217 --> 40:20.717
More than she deserved!

40:20.752 --> 40:22.734
Look, we have identified
the murder weapon.

40:22.785 --> 40:24.052
It belonged to him.

40:24.087 --> 40:25.519
You've already decided he's guilty.

40:25.570 --> 40:27.057
I don't trust you with our friend.

40:27.092 --> 40:28.491
Yeah, well, I don't trust you either.

40:28.493 --> 40:30.828
You don't want to start a war.

40:34.199 --> 40:36.867
- Clear the road.
- He's not going anywhere.

40:36.901 --> 40:39.269
- Neither are we.
- Go home!

40:40.772 --> 40:42.840
Just clear the road!

40:44.109 --> 40:45.476
Go home.

40:45.510 --> 40:48.712
[crowd murmuring]

40:48.746 --> 40:51.081
[engine turns over]

40:51.116 --> 40:54.751
[car rattling, crunching]

40:54.786 --> 40:56.520
She's doing this.

40:56.554 --> 40:58.822
That's crazy. It's an
earthquake or something.

40:58.857 --> 41:01.825
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

41:01.860 --> 41:05.162
<i>♪</i>

41:05.196 --> 41:06.830
She a witch. I told you she's a witch!

41:06.865 --> 41:08.397
There's no such thing as witches, Gomez.

41:08.399 --> 41:09.600
Then what is happening?

41:09.634 --> 41:11.502
Fiji, not this way.

41:11.536 --> 41:12.903
This won't help him.

41:12.937 --> 41:14.571
And tomorrow's a full moon.

41:14.606 --> 41:16.240
I'll be unavailable for a few days.

41:16.274 --> 41:19.576
We have got to be smart about this, Fij.

41:19.611 --> 41:21.612
Not angry.

41:21.646 --> 41:23.113
I'll help.

41:23.148 --> 41:24.748
However I can.

41:26.151 --> 41:27.684
And I think I can.

41:27.719 --> 41:28.752
[cries]

41:29.754 --> 41:31.855
[metal creaking]

41:31.890 --> 41:33.223
[siren whoops randomly]

41:33.258 --> 41:36.226
Okay. I'ma crank the car.

41:36.261 --> 41:37.861
Hurry up.

41:37.896 --> 41:40.297
- We're gonna get out of here.
- Hurry up!

41:40.331 --> 41:45.149
<i>♪ They're shutting down
all the exit lanes ♪</i>

41:45.181 --> 41:48.872
<i>♪ Means one thing ♪</i>

41:48.907 --> 41:52.643
<i>♪ Trouble's coming ♪</i>

41:52.677 --> 41:54.144
<i>♪</i>

41:54.179 --> 41:59.616
<i>♪ Maybe it's just me ♪</i>

41:59.651 --> 42:02.553
<i>♪ All the midnights of madness ♪</i>

42:02.587 --> 42:06.623
<i>♪ The darkness that
crashes and screams ♪</i>

42:06.658 --> 42:09.259
[growling and rumbling]

42:09.294 --> 42:10.894
<i>♪ Trouble's coming ♪</i>

42:10.936 --> 42:13.304
<i>♪</i>

